<subSubSection pageId="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1015,1040]" pageId="3">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Botero &amp; Almeida, 2019" authorityName="Botero &amp; Almeida" authorityYear="2019" box="[324,620,1016,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aiurasyma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santandereana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,620,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="3">Aiurasyma santandereana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[630,720,1016,1039]" pageId="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 2001" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2001" box="[875,1270,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aiurasyma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potira">
<emphasis box="[875,978,1016,1039]" italics="true" pageId="3">A. potira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[987,1270,1015,1040]" pageId="3" pagination="15 - 20" refId="ref18610" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2001) Novos taxons de Disteniidae (Coleoptera) neotropicais. Iheringia¸ Zoologia, 90, 15 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212001000100002" type="journal article" year="2001">Martins &amp; Galileo, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the deeper anterior and posterior constriction of prothorax, pronotal tubercles more elevated and entirely glabrous and shallow, posterior margin of the scutellum strongly emarginate, lighter region of the elytra reaching the scutellum, and the unicolorous legs. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2001" box="[496,601,1124,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aiurasyma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potira">
<emphasis box="[496,601,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="3">A. potira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[622,735,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[308,1283,208,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[299,1290,195,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4, Aiurasyma santandereana sp. nov., holotype, male: 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4, detail of head, frontal view. 5–8, Aiurasyma potira Martins &amp; Galileo, 2001, male: 5, detail of head, frontal view; 6, dorsal view; 7, ventral view; 8, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651532/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figs. 5–8</figureCitation>
), the constrictions of the prothorax are shallower, pronotal tubercles are less elevated, are punctate and with long setae, posterior margin of the scutellum is truncate, lighter region of the elytra does not reach the scutellum, and the legs (femora and tibiae) are bicolorous.
</paragraph>
